               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340410-204-person1332">
                  JOHN 
                  SHEPHERD
               <interp inst="t18340410-204-person1332" type="surname" value="SHEPHERD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340410-204-person1332" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340410-204-person1332" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a policeman. On the 20th of March, about ten minutes after nine o'clock in the evening I was in <placeName id="t18340410-204-crimeloc1165">Cock-alley, Norton-falgate</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18340410-204-crimeloc1165" type="placeName" value="Cock-alley, Norton-falgate"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18340410-204-crimeloc1165" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340410-204-off1163 t18340410-204-crimeloc1165"></join> - I saw a boy standing at the back of Briggs's premises - I suspected him - another joined him soon after, and when they saw us, they made off- neither of them was the prisoner - I sent the constable, and took the two boys into custody - I found a piece of lead where the boys stood - I went up stairs in a house in Cock-alley, in half an hour - I found the prisoner in bed, and this piece of lead lying about two yards from him; another boy was in bed with him - we took them both into custody - they said they knew nothing of the lead - it was concealed under the cinders in the garret - we took five persons who were in the house into custody - next morning I fitted the lead to Briggs's premises, and it tallied exactly; also the piece which I found where the boys stood - I took them all five before the magistrate - they were all discharged except the prisoner - I was present at the examination - I saw the magistrate sign the deposition which was read over to the prisoner - no threat or promise was held out to him - this is Mr. Broughton's handwriting (read) -"At the second examination, the prisoner said, the other persons knew nothing about the lead, for that he found it, and carried it there."</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340410-204-person1333">
                  ALEXANDER 
                  SCOTT
               <interp inst="t18340410-204-person1333" type="surname" value="SCOTT"></interp>
