                     <interp inst="t18340410-204-person1333" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a policeman. Shepherd's evidence is correct.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340410-204-person1334">
                  THOMAS 
                  BREESE
               <interp inst="t18340410-204-person1334" type="surname" value="BREESE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340410-204-person1334" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340410-204-person1334" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am foreman to Robert Briggs and another - the back of their premises opens into Cock-alley - I had seen the lead secure on the top of the manufactory before this happened - the party had got on the roof from the outside - it is a great height - they must have had a ladder to get up - the lead appeared quite bright and fresh - there is a soot shed adjoining the premises - they must have got on the top of the shed; the lead was cut in a very unworkmanlike manner - I have seen the prisoner about the neighbourhood.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. About eight o'clock at night, I went to bed - I went outside to do what I wanted, and saw the lead lying on the ruins - I took it up stairs and went to bed.</p>
               <p>
